review_blob: Copper pour with white head and good lacing.  Aroma is mostly caramel malt.  Flavor is very malty but with a strong bitter hop finish.  Pretty good but didnt jump out at me.
Tap at Flying Saucer.  Brown pour, great taste of malts and dark fruit.  Creamy and delicious.
Excellent.  Almost black pour.  Sweet aroma of chocolate and dark fruit.  Complex flavor includes chocolate, nuts, fruit, malt and vanilla.  Drinkable and delicious.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: This is possibly the thickest beer I have ever had.  Thick black pour.  Strong flavor of roasted malts but balanced with a little bitterness and dark fruit flavor.  Very good.

The commercial deScription says it all pretty well.  Clear orange pour, smells of toffee.  Flavor is sweet, a little smoky, alcohol comes through as it warms.  Lets not even discuss how difficult it was to find this beer.
Tap at Flying Saucer Houston.  Smells of pine, taste is bitter and hoppy.  I wasnt terribly impressed, it was to be expected but it was a one sided IPA.

Tap at Flying Saucer Houston.  Black with a brown head.  Smells of roasted malt and maybe some chocolate.  Taste is of coffee and roasted malt with a strong bitter finish.  Not much chocolate in the taste.

Tap at Rogue Alehouse in San Francisco.  Aroma was a very weak malt smell.  The flavor was malty with some dark fruit and a bit of chocolate.  Nice bitter balance but nothing about this beer really stood out.  Plus they would only pour me a half pint.  Cowards.
Had the draught.  Piney hop smell.  Flavor was great, hoppy but balanced with a nice bitter edge and aftertaste.  Very good IPA.

This is finally available in Texas! Looks as black as possible with a little brown head.  Smells of coffee, roasted malts.  Flavor was very smooth and balanced with coffee, chocolate, a little hop bitterness to balance it all out.  Very good but I liked Black Albert more.
Had it on draught.  Tasted like a watered down guinness.  No real flavors, didnt even seem like a stout.  And no, this one is not like Jamaican Guinness, which is actually good.

I enjoyed this.  Aroma of chocolate and cream.  Fairly light bodied and and copper color.  Tasted of chocolate and the typical malty bock flavors.  Seemed too light for something with "chocolate" in the name but I enjoyed it!

Dark brown pour, small head.  Strong aroma of banana and chocolate.  Flavor is the same with a good bit of wheat and yeast and some smoke and coffee.  SA needs to work on making their beers a little smoother though.
Copper pour with small white head.  Smell is sweet, grapes.  Flavor is a balanced sweet malt flavor.  Medium body, alcohol is hidden.
Brown pour with big head leaving lots of lacing.  Sweet yeast smell.  Fairly typical quad taste of malt, caramel, yeast, dark fruit and some alcohol.  Good.
Dark brown pour with tan head.  Smells of malt, berries and spice.  taste is big and complex.  Chocolate, spices, fruit, a little alcohol.
Clear blonde color.  Light yeasty aroma.  Light, drinkable flavor of fruit, hops and yeast.

Black pour with big tan head that doesnt move.  Smell of espresso coffee, brown sugar, caramel.  Flavor is huge of coffee, roasted malt, chocolate, some fruit, even a little orange.  Wow, one of the best.  Bitter aftertaste, great lacing and very drinkable.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: mahogany color. Spicy dark fruit smell. Similar taste, with bitter chocolate. Full bodied and complex.
Dark brown with a big head. Aroma of plum and malt. Flavor is dark fruit, mostly plum and roasted malt. Strong alcohol presence. Intense and very good.
Hoppy smell. Golden orange appearance with big head. Spicy and hoppy taste. Smooth feel.
Bottle from utobeer in London. Excellent beer. Tastes of oats, roasted malt, coffee, chocolate. Creamy but full bodied.

draught at in de vrede near the abbey. Simply put, fantastic. Caramel sweet smell. Taste is complex, every sip is different. Flavors of dark fruit, caramel, alcohol, very balanced and drinkable. Very smooth. Best Ive ever had.
draught in Munich. Typical brown appearance with a sweet caramel smell. Powerful caramel, plum and grape flavors.
Few bottles over the past few days in Charleston, SC.  Nice flavor: malty, nutty, chocolate.  Solid body.  Definitely enjoyed.
Golden pour.  Smells a bit of lime and hops.  Taste is a balanced hop flavor with a little lime.  Nice light summer beer.
A solid pale ale.  Aroma and flavor are both dominated by bitter hops, but the taste is balanced fairly well.
beer_name: Flying Dog Double Dog Double Pale Ale

review_blob: Dark brown pour.  Pretty straightforward taste of malt and some coffee. Enjoyable but nothing special.

Draught at Flying Saucer Houston.  Dark copper pour with big tan head.  Aroma is of strong hops.  Hops hit you immediately on first taste, but then the malty flavors, some sugary balance things out.  The bitter taste stays with you.  Doesnt really seem like a barley wine.
Sample at the brewery.  A little light in body, sweet taste of sugar and yeast.
Draft at Draught House.  Tasted of sweet caramel and sugar.  I found it enjoyable, maybe it would be more so during the cold months.  I couldnt taste any alcohol but I felt it afterwards.

I dont know how to rate this beer.  The aroma is bacon.  Nothing else, it just smells like bacon.  Tastes the same way with some malty and grape notes.   This beer is just really out there.  The flavors are strong, but not what I want a beer to taste like.
Got this at a bar in Denver.  A simple brown ale, very sweet and malty, but lacking the nut flavors of better brown ales.  Nothing really stood out, but very drinkable.
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: Draught at the brewery in Denver.  Red with white head.  Smells and tastes like raspberry juice.  Simple beer.
Draught at the brewery in Denver.  I really enjoyed this one.  This is the maltiest pale ale Ive ever had.  Definitely has the hop profile but also a sweet, cookie like, biscuity malt side.
Draught at the brewery in Denver.  Very nice IPA.  Orange hop aroma.  Flavor is similar, yet simple and balanced.
Draught at the brewery in Denver.  Aroma is sweet and hoppy.  Flavor is dominated more by the sweet malt flavors, mostly caramel.
Draught at the brewery in Denver. Well you know what you are getting with a double IPA.  Citrus hop aroma and flavor is very strong hops - piney and citrusy, sweet malt for balance.
Tap at the brewery in Denver.  Thick black appearance.  Sweet aroma.  Flavor is roasty, coffee, but with a good bit of hop to balance it out.  Impressive beer.
For some reason I thought this was worse than coors light.  I had it at my first NHL game though.
Dark brown pour with a nice head.  Got a growler at the brewery.  Sweet aroma.  Flavor has chocolate, caramel, sweet fruit.  Very nice beer.
It is difficult to rate unique beers like this.  I had it on tap at the brewery.  The flavor was mostly sour apple, lime juice, maybe a little vinegar.
Dark brown with small tan head.  Smelled interesting, fruity, malty.  Flavor had a strange spice that made it a bit sour almost? Pretty good though.
Typical hefeweizen appearance and aroma: wheat, some orange.  A bit light bodied but good overall.
Seemed malty all around to me.  Sweet malt smell and taste, but the taste was rounded out with bitter hops.  Nice, balanced beer but nothing amazing.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic Best Ale / Organically Produced Ale

review_blob: Had it on tap at Flying Saucer.  Aroma was strong of hops.  Flavor was a bit of a let down, a bit bland, typical bitter ipa flavor.  I had no idea the alcohol was so high.
Dark pour, small head.  Smells mildy of vanilla.  Vanilla is strong in the taste, and then the typical roasted malt of a porter.  Enjoyable, not great.
Dark brown pour with tan head.  Smells great of sweet fruit.  Flavor is malty, some fruit and chocolate, but a little bland I thought.  Still very good though.
Orange pour.  Smells of tart orange.  Flavor is similar, a bit of wheat and some orange.  Reminded me of a sweet tart.
Tap at Ginger Man Houston.  Cloudy pour, fruit and citrus aroma.  Flavor is typical: wheat, citrus, light and refreshing body.
